      "side": 1,
      "message": "First of all, I think we should really rename IsCQDUsingMyRuns to IsCVInCharge to add more clarity because I keep treat IsCQDUsingMyRuns \u003d true as CQD is in charge. \n\nI guess Quinten think the same way here, so I assume this question as is it possible that run is not finalized by CQDaemon, but we get CV is *NOT* in charge here and we end up never emit BQ.\n\nI feel like the answer is unfortunately yes but under race condition and it should be rare.\n\nt0: Run A is running and CQD is in charge\nt1: Run A is switch to CV in charge but the config change only populates to CQD atm\nt2: Run A finishes verification. Since CV is in charge, CQD reports verified Run to CV.\nt3: CV finalizes the Run but doesn\u0027t do BQ export because it think CQD is still in charge of Run A\nt4: CV finally realize it\u0027s in charge of Run A and it\u0027s too late :(",
